  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc6\u0ddc\u0dc3\u0dda\u0da7\u0dca \u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Approval of Glyphosate Import Gazette",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The regulations enacted under the Import and Export (Control) Act No. 1 of 1969 in relation to allowing the import of glyphosate, which is used as a weed killer for the plantation sector, was recently considered in the Finance Committee of the Government and after a long discussion, the approval of the Committee was given.",
        "This approval was received when the committee met recently (02) under the chairmanship of Dr. Harsha De Silva, Chairman of the Government Finance Committee.",
        "Thus, the Extraordinary Gazette No. 2291/44 containing these regulations is to be submitted to the Parliament tomorrow (6th) for approval. According to this gazette, import licenses for glyphosate will be issued subject to the recommendation of the pesticide registrar.",
        "The chairman of the committee also said that although the approval of the finance committee of the government has been obtained for these regulations, it will be given with conditions. He pointed out that further decisions should be taken after holding a wide discussion on the prepared report after discussing the use of glyphosate in Sri Lanka's plantation crops according to the recommendation of the finance committee.",
        "He also emphasized that bills and other bills to be submitted for Parliament's approval should be received by the Finance Committee in advance and approval should be given only after extensive discussion.",
        "Considering the possible health effects of using glyphosate as a weed killer in the plantation sector, despite banning the import of glyphosate, there was a discussion about the need to import glyphosate with restrictions or due to reasons such as the obstacles to the export of tea and rubber plantations and the need to control the Weligama coconut leaf wilt disease. Also, regarding the health and environmental impact caused by this, the MPs as well as officials expressed their opinions.",
        "Thus, the chairman of the committee emphasized the need to hold a wide discussion about this in the future and take future decisions."
      ],
